tion of Sumerian copular paratactic relative clauses, which make use of an otherwise only scarcely attested relativization strategy. At the end of the book, the reader will have a clear picture about the morphological and syntactic devices used to mark identificational, polarity and sentence focus in Sumerian, one of the oldest documented languages in the world.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access. Unless otherwise specified individually in the content, the work is licensed under the Creative Commons Attribution-NonCommercial-NoDerivatives (CC BY-NC-ND) license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/3.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Feb 2021) 0aFocus (Linguistics). 0aSumerian languagexClauses. 0aSumerian languagexGrammar. 0aSumerian languagexSyntax. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / Syntax.2bisacsh  aSumerian, copula, focus, information structure, copular clauses, grammaticalization, cuneiform languages.0 cEPUBz97831104273490 cprintz978311040169140uhttps://doi.org/10.2478/9783110401707zOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110401707zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9783110401707.jpg  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-GOA